p:
Microalgae and cyanobacteria were grown in autoclaved sterile medium at 26 ± 1 °C, with a photon flux of ca. 300 µmoles photon m
 −2 s
 −1 and 16 h light: 8 h dark photoperiod. Freshwater strains were grown in ASM-1 medium whereas marine strains were grown in f/2 medium (
 Gorham et al., 1964; 
 Guillard & Lorenzen, 1972; 
 Reynolds & Jaworski, 1978). Cultures were grown in glass balloons with 300–500 mL of culture medium for 3–6 weeks, depending on the growth rate of each strain. The cultures were stored at −80 °C until extracts production.
